EJIKEME OMENAZU Rev. Father Christogonus Chinonso Okonko of Ahiara Catholic Diocese, Imo State, has stated that God overlooked his imperfections and chose him as a Catholic priest. Rev. Okonko was speaking during the third anniversary celebration of his ordination, which took place in the Diocese on May 4, 2022. -Advertisement- “It can only be God. Who am I to be counted worthy to be ordained a priest out of many that began that journey? It is just grace. It is God’s abiding love. The devil did what it could, but God in His infinite mercy said I am his chosen one, I am grateful to Him.” Okonko also thanked those who contributed to make his dream of becoming a Rev. Father a reality. He said: “I thank all those who contributed towards my becoming a priest and still helping in the propagation of the word of God. “I pray for God’s visitation upon their lives, and God will visit them with abundant blessings of long life and prosperity.”